OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1780942271
OL,3,CFootballer Christian Eriksen collapses
OL,4,Con pitch during Denmark game
OL,6,FThe Danish team's doctor, Morten
OL,7,FBoesen, said on Sunday Eriksen had
OL,8,Fbeen briefly unconscious, but
OL,9,F"regained consciousness very quickly"
OL,10,Fand was able to walk off the pitch by
OL,11,Fhimself.
OL,13,FHe said Eriksen's pacemaker, which was
OL,14,Ffitted after his previous collapse,
OL,15,Fappeared to be "functioning as it
OL,16,Fshould".
OL,18,F"He briefly lost consciousness but
OL,19,Fregained it very quickly, and we were
OL,20,Fable to communicate with him right
OL,21,Faway," Boesen said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
